STORY TIME***

This photo is of my beautiful friend Dana from 12 years ago. She was going to a black tie event and asked me to do her makeup. At this time I wasn’t taking makeup seriously AT ALL. I would just do it for my friends whenever they asked. Her aunt was present as I was doing her makeup and asked “Do you do weddings?” I said “No! I’m not messing no brides face up on her wedding day.” And my friend said “You should do it. Your better than you think.” No confidence at all I still said no. Her aunt said “well I like your work and I’m going to put you in contact with the bride anyway.” I got booked for the wedding not knowing what the hell I’m doing for a wedding party of like 10 people. Went to a drug store and bought @lorealparis true match in every shade. Went to the beauty supply store and got the cheapest eyeshadow palette with as many colors. Ordered “MAC” brushes from eBay and I was set. I should of known I wasn’t getting 30 real “MAC” brushes for $20 😩. Prior to this wedding I had been working in banking for 5 years. I lost my job October of 2011. That wedding was Nov of 2011 and I’ve been doing makeup ever since. I prayed on it and said god I don’t know what your doing but you took my good paying job. If this is what I’m meant to be doing give me the signs and I’ll follow your lead. Every door that has opened for me it’s weird but I heard god speak to me and I followed. Don’t get me wrong it didn’t come easy, but I put in the time and hard work to be where I am in my makeup career. What is meant for you will be! Shout out to all my friends who believed in me when I didn’t believe in myself, and for letting me play on y’all face 🤣 Y’all know who y’all are! 😘 Thank you @dana_deluxe for sharing this memory with me. ♥️
What I require I reciprocate. Standards high asf

🔦Friend Spot Light!!! 🔦

Had the pleasure of glamming and being present for my sister/friend this weekend for a MAJOR accomplishment of being inducted into one of the highest honors a nurse can receive, a fellow in American Academy of Nursing. Only 3,000 of the 4 million nurses in the US have received this honor in the last 50 years. She traveled to nearly 7 countries this year alone helping thousands of men, women, and children in need of medical attention. Not to mention my friend has her doctorate. She’s also the Associate Deanof the Undergraduate Nursing Program at NYU.  COME ON NOW!!!! 🙌🏽 @dr_g_saidso You are prime example of going after what you want and you did just that. I stepped out!
The girls favorite! Brown Smokey 🤎 #BDayGlam

I know that getting your makeup done can be a very overwhelming feeling. Especially when you’re not someone who wears or is into makeup. All it takes is the right person to break you out of your shell. Doesn’t mean you have to wear it everyday but definitely open to wearing makeup when necessary (Like your daughter’s wedding). It is very important for me to be a versatile artist. I know what I see and want when I look at a client but what is it that you want from this makeup session. We all know when you look good you feel good and that is my ultimate goal. I want every client of mine getting out of my chair looking and feeling their absolute BEST! This very moment is why I love what I do!♥️
